      "writtenOn": "2018-06-01T01:45:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that there\u0027s basically two options, either remove the self-deleting aspect of threads or add some sort of reference counting.\n\nFor reference counting, shared_ptr by itself isn\u0027t sufficient because it could potentially change which thread calls the destructor, and increment/decrement isn\u0027t thread safe.  shared_ptr+weak_ptr is still not thread-safe, but ensures that the destructor is called on the correct thread.\n\nWhat I recommend is to move all Thread state into a ThreadState struct, and wrap that in something like atomic_shared_ptr, if available, or shared_ptr+lock.  Then when performing an operation on state make sure you have a local reference to it to increment the refcount and operate on that.",
      "parentUuid": "01ac6479_1a9a1171",
